{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f6014a45-b6a9-48a0-8fe8-d5833d45b62c","content":"### 3. Other v4 changes to watch for\n\n| Area | What changed |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallelism** | Tests run in parallel **by default**. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or `DoNotParallelize` if your tests have shared state. |\n| **TestInitialize/TestCleanup** | Now run **per-test** even for `[DataTestMethod]` rows (previously was once for all rows in some scenarios). |\n| **Assertions** | `Assert.AreEqual` on floating-point types is stricter — old tests with loose epsilon checks may fail. |\n| **Timeout** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` cooperatively instead of `Thread.Abort`. Long-running tests that ignored cancellation may hang instead of aborting. |\n| **`[DynamicData]`** | Source generators now validate the shape at build time — previously-silent mismatches become compile errors. |\n\nThe parallelism default is the one that catches the most people. If you see intermittent failures after upgrading, that's likely it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"446fb723-57e3-4315-bb04-4ac943c450c9","outputTokens":269,"requestId":"E3C2:1ED62C:1D2C23F:20C9AE5:6A053F31"},"id":"5b54e361-75b4-45bc-9aa2-ba31feaf9bfb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:19:22.033Z","parentId":"e90463dd-13cf-41be-8d16-abd6f9020a49"}
